intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of the course students will be able to:
Describe and compare capabilities of various communication technologies and techniques;
Point out differences between networks of different scale, and how these affect their design;
Describe the issues in connecting heterogeneous networks;
Describe importance of layering, and the OSI reference model;
Detail demands of different applications on quality of service requirements for the underlying communication network;
Demonstrate an understanding of the design and operation of an IP network, such as the Internet, and explain the purpose and function of its various components;
Write simple low-level communication software, showing awareness of good practice for correct and secure programming.
